    "description": "Muraki Corporation engages in the wholesale of car care, and automobile repair parts and related products in Japan. The company provides aftermarket parts, including oil and air elements, radiator valves, wiper blades, batteries, and air conditioner filters; and auto chemical products, such as window washer and brake fluids, oil and air conditioner related chemicals, body and glass coatings, and supercoolants. It also sells automotive maintenance equipment comprising engine oil changers, air conditioning gas refreshers, balancer, car wash machines, lift, and ATF and tire changers. It also offers products, such as supplies, signs and store decoration LEDs, car wash detergents, grease and fat pollution prevention cleaners, AdBlue and many promotional goods. In addition, it provides after-sales and maintenance services. The company offers its products to customers, such as service stations. Muraki Corporation was founded in 1946 and is headquartered in Tama, Japan."
